laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Serologic Testing for HIV, Hepatitis B and C Virus, Borrelia burgdorferi, and West Nile Virus

laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive with a speckled pattern at a titer of 1:40 (normal value, <1:32)
No white cells, 24 red cells/mm³, protein 1.50 g/L (normal range, 0.15 to 0.45), glucose 3.1 mmol/L (normal range, 4.0 to 6.0)
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Second lumbar puncture revealed 16 white cells/mm³, protein elevated at 1.20 g/L, glucose level 4.2 mmol/L.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Low-amplitude median and tibial motor responses on the right side, normal conduction velocities.
Fibrillation potentials and reduced recruitment in right deltoid, biceps, triceps, vastus lateralis, and adductor magnus muscles.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Ultrasonography of the Abdomen and Pelvis
laboratory_examinations.findings: Multiple solid, hypoechoic vascular masses in the uterus and right ovary.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up ultrasonography showed a single complex vascular lesion now measuring 4.5 cm.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: MRI of the Brain and Spine with Gadolinium
laboratory_examinations.findings: Hyperdense foci in left caudate and lentiform nuclei, no cord compression or nerve-root impingement.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up MRI showed enhanced multiple nerve roots suggestive of subacute-to-chronic inflammatory polyradiculopathy.
Follow-up lumbar puncture revealed 26 white cells/mm³, protein level of 2.60 g/L, and glucose level of 3 mmol/L.
